The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, March 27, 2003 				 Samsung arms set to merge
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, March 26: The Delhi High Court today paved the way for the merger of Samsungs two Indian arms without a meeting of either vendors or creditors, a normal pre-condition for such mergers.																								The high court, which is yet to give its final approval, has been hearing a plea from Samsung Electronics Company of South Korea for permission to merge Samsung Electronics India Information and Telecommunications Limited, a 100 per cent subsidiary of the parent company, with another wholly-owned subsidiary, Samsung Electronics India Ltd, to create a Rs 2,800 crore electronic and IT conglomerate.																								The name of the new entity to be created after the merger is yet to be decided. 
